						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Anonymous wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">One thing I was thinking about was sticking on a SPI flash for recording and playing back controller input movies, but that really needs to be an in-console job, so I could hook /NMI for good sync <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />  Would people be interested in this?</div>
<br />If you have access to the cart slot, you can hook NMI by looking for three writes in a row (which <em>only</em> happens on an interrupt) followed by reads from $FFFA and $FFFB. In practice, you can get away with just looking for a read from $FFFA.</div>

